2 (ii) one member must have has experience in community planning;
3 (iii) one member must have has experience in historic preservation;
4 (iv) two members must have has broad experience in business;
5 (v) one member must be is a member of the tourism advisory council established in 2-15-1816;
6 (vi) one member must be is a Montana historian; and or
7 (vii) two members must be is from the public at large.
8 (3) Except for the initial appointments, members appointed by the governor under subsection
9 (2)(a) shall serve 3-year terms. Members appointed by the president of the senate and the speaker of the
10 house or by the governor under subsection (2)(b) shall serve 2-year terms. If a vacancy occurs, the appointing
11 authority shall make an appointment for the unexpired portion of the term.
12 (4) (a) The commission may employ:
13 (i) an executive director who has general responsibility for the selection and management of
14 commission staff, developing recommendations for the purchase of property, and overseeing the management
15 of acquired property;
16 (ii) a curator who is responsible for the display and preservation of the acquired property; and
17 (iii) other staff that the commission and the executive director determine are necessary to manage
18 and operate commission properties.
19 (b) The commission shall prescribe the duties and annual salary of the executive director, the
20 curator, and other commission staff.
21 (4) In compliance with the state pay plan, the department shall provide all staff and services to the
22 commission that the commission, in conjunction with the department, determines are necessary for carrying out
23 the commission's programs and statutory requirements. The department shall assess the commission for
24 reasonable costs."
25
26 NEW SECTION. Section 2. Transition. The reduction of the number of Montana heritage
27 preservation and development commission members from 14 to 9 as provided in [section 1(2)(a)] must occur as
28 the terms of the existing members appointed by the governor end and the members are not reappointed.
